Example
Create and use static properties and methods:
<?php
class MyClass {
public static $str = "Hello World!";
public static function hello() {
echo MyClass::$str;
}
}
echo MyClass::$str;
echo "<br>";
echo MyClass::hello();
?>

Definition and Usage
The
static
keyword is used to declare properties and methods of a class as static. Static
properties and methods can be used without creating an instance of the class.
The
static
keyword is also used to declare variables in a function which keep their value
after the function has ended.
Related Pages
Read more about static methods in our
PHP OOP - Static Methods Tutorial
.
Read more about static properties in our
PHP OOP - Static Properties Tutorial
.
More Examples
Example
Use a static variable in a function:
<?php
function add1() {
static $number = 0;
$number++;
return $number;
}
echo add1();
echo "<br>";
echo add1();
echo "<br>";
echo 
  add1();
?>

